/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 738.00 Tm
(321-500) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 724.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 696.00 Tm
(The intended scientific discipline is important: do not train or tune on OOD lengths.) Tj
/F1 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 654.00 Tm
(1. Research Question) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 612.00 Tm
(The main question is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 584.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 570.00 Tm
(Can small Transformer policies trained with PPO/GRPO and oracle process rewards) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 556.00 Tm
(learn length-generalizing algorithms for formal languages better than) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 542.00 Tm
(terminal-only RL?) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 528.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 500.00 Tm
(The hypothesis is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 472.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 458.00 Tm
(process reward -> better state tracking -> more algorithmic policy ->) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 444.00 Tm
(better length generalization) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 430.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 402.00 Tm
(The point is not merely to obtain high training accuracy. The point is to see whether the) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 388.00 Tm
(learned policy extrapolates from short inputs to much longer ones.) Tj
/F1 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 346.00 Tm
(2. General Problem Setup) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 304.00 Tm
(Each task defines an input sequence:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 276.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 262.00 Tm
(x = \(x_1, x_2, ..., x_n\)) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 248.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 220.00 Tm
(an oracle intermediate state trace:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 192.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 178.00 Tm
(s = \(s_1, s_2, ..., s_n\)) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 164.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 136.00 Tm
(and a final answer:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 108.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 94.00 Tm
(y_final) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 80.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 478 30 Tm
