/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 738.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 724.00 Tm
(R = lambda_p R_process + lambda_T R_terminal) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 710.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 682.00 Tm
(where `lambda_p` is `process_weight` and `lambda_T` is `terminal_weight`.) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 654.00 Tm
(The three RL reward modes are:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 626.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 612.00 Tm
(terminal-only:          R = R_terminal) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 598.00 Tm
(process-only:           R = R_process) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 584.00 Tm
(process-plus-terminal:  R = lambda_p R_process + lambda_T R_terminal) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 570.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 528.00 Tm
(4. Task 1: Parity) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 486.00 Tm
(The parity language is the set of binary strings with even parity.) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 458.00 Tm
(Input symbols:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 430.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 416.00 Tm
(x_t in {0, 1}) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 402.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 374.00 Tm
(The hidden state is a parity bit:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 346.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 332.00 Tm
(p_0 = 0) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 318.00 Tm
(p_t = p_{t-1} XOR x_t) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 304.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 276.00 Tm
(The trace is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 248.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 234.00 Tm
(p_1 p_2 ... p_n) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 220.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 192.00 Tm
(The final answer is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 164.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 150.00 Tm
(p_n) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 136.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 108.00 Tm
(In the implementation, states are emitted as `P0` and `P1`.) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 80.00 Tm
(The process reward is:) Tj
/F1 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 478 30 Tm
