/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 724.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 710.00 Tm
(R_process = \(1/n\) sum_{t=1}^n 1[hat_p_t = p_t]) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 696.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 668.00 Tm
(The terminal reward is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 640.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 626.00 Tm
(R_terminal = 1[hat_p_final = p_n]) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 612.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 584.00 Tm
(Parity is a regular language and should be solvable with one bit of memory. It is a sanity-) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 570.00 Tm
(check task for algorithmic state tracking.) Tj
/F1 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 528.00 Tm
(5. Task 2: Modular Counting) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 486.00 Tm
(The modular counting task asks whether the number of `1` symbols is divisible by `k`.) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 458.00 Tm
(The implementation supports:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 430.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 416.00 Tm
(k = 3) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 402.00 Tm
(k = 5) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 388.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 360.00 Tm
(The state is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 332.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 318.00 Tm
(c_0 = 0) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 304.00 Tm
(c_t = \(c_{t-1} + x_t\) mod k) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 290.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 262.00 Tm
(The final accept condition is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 234.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 220.00 Tm
(accept iff c_n = 0) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 206.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 178.00 Tm
(The process reward is:) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 150.00 Tm
(```text) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 136.00 Tm
(R_process = \(1/n\) sum_{t=1}^n 1[hat_c_t = c_t]) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 122.00 Tm
(```) Tj
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 94.00 Tm
(The terminal reward is:) Tj
/F1 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 478 30 Tm
